alyzing the political differences underlying the controversies. Students of education, history, and politics can benefit from his contribution to the re-assessment of this turbulent period in English educational history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEducationzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aEducatorszGreat BritainvBiography. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aEducation. 4aPolitical Science. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978088920753040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889207530423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889207530/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles